# 🔹 Bubble Sort

Bubble Sort repeatedly compares adjacent elements and swaps them if they are in the wrong order.

---

## Algorithm

For array:

```text
5 1 4 2
```

### Pass 1

Compare 5 & 1 → Swap

```text
1 5 4 2
```

Compare 5 & 4 → Swap

```text
1 4 5 2
```

Compare 5 & 2 → Swap

```text
1 4 2 5
```

Largest element reaches the end after one pass.

---

## Bubble Sort Code

```c
for(i=0;i<n-1;i++)
{
    for(j=0;j<n-i-1;j++)
    {
        if(a[j]>a[j+1])
        {
            swap(a[j],a[j+1]);
        }
    }
}
```

---

## Complexity

### Best Case

Already sorted (using optimization)

[
O(n)
]

---

### Average Case

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Worst Case

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Space Complexity

[
O(1)
]

---

### Stable?

✅ Yes

---

### In-place?

✅ Yes

