# 🔹 Selection Sort

Selection Sort repeatedly selects the minimum element and places it in the correct position.

---

Example

```text
5 2 8 1
```

Find minimum:

```text
1
```

Swap with first element.

Continue for remaining elements.

---

## Code

```c
for(i=0;i<n-1;i++)
{
    min=i;

    for(j=i+1;j<n;j++)
    {
        if(a[j]<a[min])
            min=j;
    }

    swap(a[i],a[min]);
}
```

---

## Complexity

### Best Case

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Average Case

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Worst Case

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Stable?

❌ No

---

### In-place?

✅ Yes

---

# 🔹 Insertion Sort

Builds a sorted portion one element at a time.

---

Example

```text
5 3 4 1
```

Insert:

3 before 5

```text
3 5 4 1
```

Insert:

4 between 3 and 5

```text
3 4 5 1
```

Continue.

---

## Code

```c
for(i=1;i<n;i++)
{
    key=a[i];
    j=i-1;

    while(j>=0 && a[j]>key)
    {
        a[j+1]=a[j];
        j--;
    }

    a[j+1]=key;
}
```

---

## Complexity

### Best Case

Already sorted

[
O(n)
]

---

### Average Case

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Worst Case

Reverse sorted

[
O(n^2)
]

---

### Stable?

✅ Yes

---

### In-place?

✅ Yes

